25|$|Clients hold a <b>margin</b> <b>account</b> {{with the}} exchange, {{and every day}} the swings {{in the value of}} their {{positions}} is added to or deducted from their <b>margin</b> <b>account.</b> If the <b>margin</b> <b>account</b> gets too low, they have to replenish it. In this way {{it is highly unlikely that}} the client will not be able to fulfill his obligations arising from the contracts. As the clearing house is the counterparty to all their trades, they only have to have one <b>margin</b> <b>account.</b> This is in contrast with OTC derivatives, where issues such as margin accounts have to be negotiated with all counterparties.|$|E
