2500|$|If the <b>margin</b> <b>account</b> goes below {{a certain}} value {{set by the}} Exchange, then a margin call is made and the account owner must {{replenish}} the <b>margin</b> <b>account.</b> This process is known as marking to market. Thus on the delivery date, the amount exchanged is not the specified price on the contract but the spot value (i.e. the original value agreed upon, since any gain or loss has already been previously settled by marking to market). Upon marketing the strike price is often reached and creates lots of income for the [...] "caller." ...|$|E
25|$|Customer margin Within {{the futures}} industry, {{financial}} guarantees required of both buyers and sellers of futures contracts and sellers of options contracts to ensure fulfillment of contract obligations. Futures Commission Merchants are responsible for overseeing customer <b>margin</b> <b>accounts.</b> <b>Margins</b> are determined {{on the basis of}} market risk and contract value. Also referred to as performance bond margin.|$|R
